page.title: 03WALSDEN Houses
page.content: In{Walsden}there are quite a few different types of houses.{Back to {back}houses are the most common. These houses are called back to back because they are two houses with their backs joined to each other. There are also some houses called {over and unders.}These houses are built on hills and they have two storeys. Each storey is a different house and each has its own door. The second storey has a door on top of the hill and the first storey has a door at the bottom. There are also some modern houses in Walsden, most are{bungalows} although there are a few{detached}and {semi-detached}houses that are modern. Some{flats}have been built fairly recently and some people are converting old houses into modern flats.
